    <h2 style="font-family: verdana">About Russia;</h2>
    <blockquote style="font-family: courier">
      Russia is the largest country in the world, spanning Eastern Europe and
      northern Asia. It covers 11 time zones and shares borders with 14
      countries, including China, Ukraine, and Kazakhstan. It has coastlines
      along the Arctic Ocean, Pacific Ocean, and several seas. The capital and
      largest city is Moscow, while other major cities include Saint Petersburg,
      Novosibirsk, and Yekaterinburg. Russia has a population of about 145
      million people and is a federal semi-presidential republic, with a
      president as its head of state and a prime minister overseeing the
      government.
    </blockquote>
